  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Klebsiella pneumoniae is one of the most common pathogens causing nosocomial infection.
      Recently, the emergency of Carbapenem-Resistant Klebsiella pneumoniae (CRKP) had cause the
      clinical therapy be very difficult. However, there is not much empirical data as to the
      prevalence, risk factors, characteristics, and the rationality of the current therapy for the
      CRKP infection. Thus, the study was aimed to investigate the epidemiology and risk factors,
      characteristics, and the rationality of the current therapy for the CRKP infection.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      All the patients with culture positive of Klebsiella pneumoniae were screened and reported to
      the the clinical doctors and confirmed by them. And the clinical characteristics of the
      patiens, such as baseline data, outcomes etc, were recorded. Finially, to find the
      prevalence, risk factors, characteristics, and the rationality of the current therapy for the
      CRKP infection
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
